edia, appear to escalate or de-escalate sectarian tensions caused by these hybrid media events. It also explores whether citizen activity on these online platforms has the potential to contribute to peacebuilding in Northern Ireland.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDemonstrationszNorthern Ireland. 0aSocial mediaxPolitical aspectszNorthern Ireland. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh  aFacebook.  aNorthern Ireland.  aTwitter.  aYouTube.  acontentious politics.  aparades.  aprotests.  aqualitative.  asocial media.  asocial movements.1 aReilly, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615294740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526152947423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526152947/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles